Boil a large #pot of water for the @quinoa{170%g}.

Stir in the quinoa and @vegetable stock{1/2%sachet} and bring back to the boil. Cook until
the quinoa has doubled in size and the seed has visibly split, ~{12-15%minutes}.
Drain in a #sieve and return to the #pot, off the heat. Cover with a #lid and set aside.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Trim the @green beans{75%g}, then chop into thirds.

Chop the @broccolini{75%g} into thirds.

Halve the @chilli{1} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Place a #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the shallot, green beans, broccolini and @prawns{180%g}. Season with salt and
pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and half the chilli
(use less if you don't like spice). Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Pop in @korma curry paste{1%sachet}, @creme fraiche{110%g}, @vegetable stock{1/2%sachet},
@water{2%tbsp} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

> Double water and sugar quantities for 4 servings.

Cover and simmer until prawns are cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if needed. Once ready, season to taste
with salt and pepper.

Divide the quinoa between #bowls{}.

Top with the prawn curry.

Scatter over the remaining chilli.

> Use less chilli if you don't like spice.